Sighting reported by Matt Mundle, Commanding officer CCGS Bickerton:On Thursday August 3 we observed a possible right whale in position 44 57.7__N 061 21.2__W.  This was during a SAR Tasking and due to the workload at the time we were unable to get any pictures.  We checked out pictures online when we returned to base and as a crew agreed that what was sighted was a right whale.  Only one whale was seen at a time, however it is possible that there was more than one due to the frequency of water spouts (blow offs?) observed.
